  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This randomized clinical trial investigates the effect of the extracorporeal shockwave
      therapy (ESWT) on periodontal and endodontical parameters. The ESWT is a scientifically
      approved non invasive method to influence bone turnover and tissue regeneration. The
      hypotheses of this trial are that ESWT increases the periodontal stability of orthodontically
      aligned teeth as well as increase the blood flow. Increasing the periodontal stability would
      reduce the retention phase, relapse risk and accelerate the rehabilitation of the surrounding
      tissues.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
